             Ubuntu / Debian packaging for the biosensor solver

This package creates source and binary DEB packages for the biosensor modelling
software (https://github.com/kape1395/biosensor.solver-2D). For the Ubuntu case,
the main idea is to use Ubuntu PPA (https://launchpad.net/~kape1395/+archive/bio)
for building binary packages so only source package is needed for this.

The following steps should be ferformed for each upstream release (lets say
0.6.6) if packaging details are not changing between releases:
  1. Update version numbers in the build.properties file. Example of the
     contents:
         upstream_version=0.6.6
         packaging_suffix=-0ubuntu3
  2. Update debian/changelog file. For example:
         $ dch -v 0.6.6-0ubuntu3 "Packaging upstream release version 0.6.6."
  3. Invoke ./build.sh. You can to it by executing main target in the Makefile:
         $ make
     This will checkout corresponding tag of the upstream component and
     create source distribution file (*.tar.gz).
  4. Upload source package to the Ubuntu PPA. This can be done as follows:
         $ ( cd build && dput ppa:kape1395/bio biosensor_*_source.changes )
  5. Create tag, if build was successfull. Tag name should match package
     version. In this case it can be created as follows:
         $ git add build.properties debian/changelog
         $ git commit -m "Packaging upstream release version 0.6.6."
         $ git tag 0.6.6-0ubuntu3 -m "Packaging upstream release version 0.6.6."
  6. Publish source code changes by pushing them to the github:
         $ git push github 0.6.6-0ubuntu3 master

If packaging details should be changed, one should modify contents of the debian
directory acordingly.

Apart from the Ubuntu PPA my local repository exists for storing Ubuntu and
Debian packages. The repository can be found at http://karolis.5grupe.lt/repos-deb/.
This repository is managed using reprepro. For more information I should look 
at /home/www/repos-deb/README.


For using above mentioned repositories you can add the following (or similar)
lines to the /etc/apt/sources.list file:
    deb http://karolis.5grupe.lt/repos-deb natty main
    deb-src http://karolis.5grupe.lt/repos-deb natty main
  or
    deb http://ppa.launchpad.net/kape1395/bio/ubuntu oneiric main 
    deb-src http://ppa.launchpad.net/kape1395/bio/ubuntu oneiric main 

Add the repository key to a keystore,
    wget http://karolis.5grupe.lt/repos-deb/karolis-debian-repository.gpg -O - | sudo apt-key add -

You can use apt-get to install or upgrade the biosensor package:
    sudo apt-get update
    sudo apt-get install biosensor

The follwing are several important links used when creating this package:
    http://www.debian.org/doc/debian-policy/index.html
    http://www.debian.org/doc/manuals/maint-guide/
    http://www.debian.org/doc/manuals/repository-howto/repository-howto.en.html
    https://help.ubuntu.com/community/AptMoveHowto
    http://www.eyrie.org/~eagle/notes/debian/build-tools.html
    https://wiki.ubuntu.com/PackagingGuide/Complete
    https://help.launchpad.net/Packaging/PPA/BuildingASourcePackage

